    "notes": "Vendor: QIAGEN, Taq DNA Polymerase / Taq PCR Core Kit (Cat. 201203). Standard (non-hot-start) Taq, so no chemical activation step: a single 94 C / 3 min initial denaturation. Setup here is scaled to 50 uL from QIAGEN's 100 uL handbook table (components scale proportionally). Annealing: ~5 C below the primer Tm, 50-68 C range. The 55 C shown is a placeholder starting point. Cycles 25-35. Extension 1 min/kb at 72 C. Optional MgCl2 titration 1.5-5.0 mM; optional Q-Solution for GC-rich templates. Template <= 1 ug. Source: QIAGEN Taq PCR Handbook (https://www.qiagen.com/en-US/resources/download/KitHandbook/en-taq-pcr-handbook)"
